1995): 240-9[5] Brewer GJ, Yuzbasiyan-Gurkan V, Johnson V, Dick RD, Wang Y "Treatment of Wilson''s disease with zinc: XI. Interaction with other anticopper agents." J Am Coll Nutr 12 (1993): 26-30[6] Osman MA, Patel RB, Schuna A, Sundstrom WR, Welling PG "Reduction in oral penicillamine absorption by food, antacid and ferrous sulfate." Clin Pharmacol Ther 33 (1983): 465-70[7] "Product Information. Cuprimine (penicillamine)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.', 'Auranofin, Aurothioglucose, Sodium aurothiomalate', 'Lidocaine, Diltiazem, Tetracaine, Fluocinolone acetonide, Hydrocortisone, Fluocinonide, Isosorbide dinitrate, Zinc chloride, Procaine, Betamethasone, Fluorometholone, More', 1767369485);
